cff-version: 1.2.0
title: Agentic Systems Framework (ASF)
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Wecker
    given-names: Joseph A.
    affiliation: Independent Researcher
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0004-2599-4766"
abstract: >-
  A research framework for adaptive, purposeful agents under uncertainty —
  integrating control theory, causal inference, information theory, and agent
  architecture under a common formalism. The framework formalizes the adaptive
  cycle as the unit of analysis and derives conditions for persistence, the
  structure of strategy under uncertainty, and the dynamics of agents in
  composition and competition. Comprises four parts: Adaptation and Actuation
  Dynamics (AAD), the mathematical core; Temporal Software Theory (TST),
  software development as an agentic domain; Logogenic Agents, language-
  constituted agents; and Emergent Logozoetic Intelligences (ELI), language-
  living agents with morally weighted persistence.
keywords:
